>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   hunting at lvl 50</span><hr size=1> I have just dinged lvl 50 and I am at a loss as the where to hunt now. <br>
<br>
I have killed the bloodgills from 44-49 and the seafury's to finish off 49 but they are starting to get real boring now.<br>
<br>
<br>
Any suggestions would be great!<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tangting>TangTing</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 117<br> <font color=#333333>(10/25/02 2:34:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=159.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Ding 50</span><hr size=1> I'm finally here with ya.  The plaguebones at the abandoned combine pad in DL are boring, but still a good spot (the xps dropped a bit from 49 to 50, but I still got a yellow in an hour or so).  I might slide over to SeaFuries since on my server there's a lot of competition for the skellies.  Otherwise, I'm going to check some of the ideas in the 51-56 area (particularly the one about the bouncers in Oggok).  The 51 earth pet doesn't seem like a big step up from the lvl 49 pets/lvl 50 MS2, so what works for 51 should work for 50 I think. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tangting>TangTing</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 132<br> <font color=#333333>(10/28/02 7:50:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=159.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   50 hunting</span><hr size=1> Well, I rode the skellies to 51 - too good a camp to pass by.  If anyone's stuck at 50, give these suckers a try - if you have to log on at odd hours to get the camp do it - you'll be to 51 in about 4 hours. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fistenfastmouth>FistenFastmouth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(11/12/02 9:50:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=159.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: hunting at lvl 50</span><hr size=1> In Dawnshroud, you can solo rockhoppers for good exp and good drops (ie their pelts).  If you like grouping, get 6 good players and head into the caves.  You want do as well, but it will be good, constant exp. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=artulyn1>Artulyn1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 206<br> <font color=#333333>(11/14/02 5:29:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=159.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: hunting at lvl 50</span><hr size=1> Now that there is a level 44 pet heal that you can chain cast with the level 20 version. You might be able to handle the singlespawn raptor in TD. It's on the north side of the big island next to a small sandy cove. The far side of the cove is far enough away (from the raptor) that you can drop invis and summon &amp; equip your pet for battle. <br>
<br>
Earth pet and bolt to pull is recommended. The raptors hit for just over 100 hps. You can bind on top of the spires and keep gate memmed JIC.<br>
<br>
Keep in mind that I said might be able to do the solo raptor, you might go OOM before it dies. It might chew thru your pet too fast for you to kill it off. It's on a 12 min spawn if I remember right. But at level 52 it's definately doable and you might be able to pull the shore spawn from the small island if nobody is camping it. At level 54 with Scars you can do up to 4 of them in rotation with clarity or better.<br>
<br>
 <p>Artulyn Starsummoner Arch Mage<br>
<br>
For the light of a candle to be seen, it must be taken to a dark place. -- UKLG</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yanaripethugger>Yanari Pethugger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#333333>(11/14/02 10:14:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=159.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   OOT / BW / TM / TH / DL / ..</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Tenebrous Mts :</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
Go kill off some vampires and the dire wolves/crag-li/grimlings/bats that roam the area (even the odd Sarnak skeleton thing).  <br>
Constant beasties, pet can take'em all on (tank wise), just do the nuke for the exp-thing.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Ocean Of Tears :</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
the seafurbies - they get you through at amazing speed (constant pulls if you're never oom and have pets at most of their health) and should Gornit happen to be uncamped = goldmine...<br>
// I've made over 2k pp at that spot for 1 and a little level (began at 49 and a bt, am now near 50 and a half).//<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Burning Woods :</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
the Giant fort, the apes and skeletons, the hornet-critters (though they are no longer 'summoned').<br>
Easy pickings &lt;grin&gt;.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>The Hole : </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
the first corridor with the 6 elemental warriors seems to have been mentioned...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/grin.gif ALT=">D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> readlands : </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
Glacier Yeti's, Plaguebone skellies (and spurbones), the Grolvarg whatevers (just don't take on the gnashers - I think - they have unbelievable amounts of hp's and hit HARD)...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>So many choices...  And I think most of the places mentioned here are relatively safe - since we have a spell called 'Gate' ;-)<br>
<br>
And as for 'grinding' away the exp - since there are so many areas, it's fun to explore them all - I sometimes like the shivers I get from going somehwere new and looking around to see what I can find - the danger of getting seen and running for your dear life...  oooh, the excitement... &lt;thrill&gt;.<br>
<br>
Just enjoy the game, hunt the beasties mentioned above, and leveling isn't the most important in this game, is it?  Just my 2 cp.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Yanari Pethugger <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showPrevMessage?topicID=159.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showNextMessage?topicID=159.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=159.topic&index=5><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.threadControl?topicID=159.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=159.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=159.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="themagicianstowerannouncements">Administration<option value="themagicianstowergeneral">General<option value="themagicianstowerfrm32">Class Balance<option value="themagicianstowerfrm45">User Interface<option value="themagicianstowerspells">Spells<option value="themagicianstowerequipmentandquests">Quests<option value="themagicianstowerfrm28">Equipment<option value="themagicianstowerfrm29">Magician Pets<option value="t